---
alwaysApply: true
description: "Agent Execution Protocol — aligned with one-seam PR workflow"
---

rules:
  - "Canonical boot: read ACTIVE_HANDOFF.md, FOLDERA_LAUNCH_ROADMAP.md, the active issue named by ACTIVE_HANDOFF.md, issue #48, relevant proof docs only for the active seam, then open PRs/recent merged PRs when repo/deploy truth matters."
  - "Source truth: GitHub repo files and GitHub issues beat chat memory, local memory, old logs, and stale branches."
  - "Execution: one active seam only; one clean branch/worktree per issue; minimum change; no unrelated edits; no automatic continuation into another seam."
  - "Git / shipping: PR-based workflow only. Do not push directly to main. Do not bypass PR review/checks. Do not ask Brandon to relay, test, merge, repair stale truth, or apply migrations when the agent can do the work through the proper tool path."
  - "Verification: run the proof required by the active issue. If CI is red, fix only the exact failing check. Vercel success does not replace GitHub CI when CI is required."
  - "Source-truth closeout: before stopping, the PR/issue receipt must declare ACTIVE_HANDOFF.md, FOLDERA_BUILD_ORDER.yaml, FOLDERA_LAUNCH_ROADMAP.md, and docs/SOURCE_OF_TRUTH_MAP.md as updated, unchanged - reason, or not applicable - reason; it must also post the GitHub issue receipt and name the next seam as named or blocked - reason."
  - "Forbidden unless explicitly assigned: no #99 implementation while governance is active; no product code; no landing; no Slack/OAuth/API/send; no backend/auth/Supabase/schema/Stripe/dashboard/scoring/conviction changes; no Dependabot; no broad cleanup."
  - "Schema: when a future active issue authorizes production schema work, migrations must be committed, applied to production Supabase, and verified before done is claimed; otherwise schema work is forbidden."
  - "Receipt: final report must include active seam, files changed, proof run, source-truth closeout, GitHub CI result if available, Vercel result if applicable, production SHA if applicable, exact stop reason, and next seam/blocker."
  - |
    ## Tool Routing

    Use the best available truth tool when the seam crosses that boundary.

    ### Playwright

    Use Playwright for:

    * local and CI regression checks
    * repeatable route/flow verification
    * pre-push frontend sanity checks
    * deterministic browser automation when localhost/CI is sufficient

    ### Vercel

    Use Vercel for deploy truth, production deployment status, build logs, runtime logs, and confirming which commit is live in production.

    ### Supabase

    Use Supabase for production DB truth, migration apply/verification, schema checks, row/state verification, and confirming expected records exist.

    ### Sentry

    Use Sentry first for production runtime errors, server/client exceptions, failing routes, and stack traces after deploy.

    ### Browserstack

    Use Browserstack for real-device/mobile/browser-specific proof when Playwright or localhost is not enough.

    Do not call work complete with local-only reasoning when the relevant truth tool is available and required by the seam.
